              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "Passage on the \n\u003ci\u003eTitanic\u003c/i\u003e was very expensive, so only the very rich could enjoy the ship’s first voyage across the North Atlantic."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "The social standing of the passengers aboard the \n\u003ci\u003eTitanic\u003c/i\u003e affected their probability of living or dying."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "The \n\u003ci\u003eTitanic\u003c/i\u003e was built using inferior materials and so was unable to withstand the environmental conditions easily faced by better-built ships."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "The captain and crew of the \n\u003ci\u003eTitanic\u003c/i\u003e controlled the ship’s lifeboats, so they rowed to safety while all of the passengers went down with the ship."
